ous infections.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Iowa Department\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"Natural Resources specialists\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2022}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2036}, {\"ngram\": \"beaches\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"poor water quality\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"intestinal problems\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"serious infections\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Claire Michel's experience shows, poor water quality should not be brushed aside and taken lightly.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Michel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"poor water quality\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contaminated water can lead even healthy young people to need medical treatment.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contaminated water\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"even healthy young people\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"medical treatment\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is how the River Seine's pollution stats look when compared with some Iowa beaches, where the DNR has said at various times that swimming is not recommended because of the contamination.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2348, \"end\": 2359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \