": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"100 milliliters\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Iowa angle shows these readings from tests on July 30 or 31: \\u2022 Hickory Grove Park, Story County - 24,000 MPN/100mL \\u2022 Edson Park beach, Buena Vista County - 20,000 \\u2022 Awaysis beach, Storm Lake - 9,200 \\u2022 Bel Air beach, Buena Vista County - 3,900 \\u2022 Big Creek State Park, Polk County - 3,400 \\u2022 Gray's Lake, Des Moines - 3,000 \\u2022 Lake Iowa Park, Iowa County - 2,900 \\u2022 Lake Ahquabi State Park, Warren County: 2,100 \\u2022 Sandy Hollow Park, Sioux County - 1,500 \\u2022 Chautauqua beach, Storm Lake - 750 \\u2022 Lacey-Keosauqua State Park, Van Buren County - 660 \\u2022 Lake Wapello State Park, Davis County - 600 \\u2022 Lake of Three Fires State Park, Taylor County - 590 \\u2022 Beeds Lake, Franklin County - 540 \\u2022 Union Grove State Park, Tama County - 470 \\u2022 Lake Darling State Park, Washington County - 470 Unlike the Olympics, these comparisons between Paris and Iowa draw attention to persistent problems in our state that no one wants to celebrate.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 3645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 2798, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.9993114646608182, \"rank\": 0.0006870491240123192, \"text\": \"Story County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 2833, \"end\": 2838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edson_River\", \"score\": 0.9999996220127091, \"rank\": 3.454543369854899e-07, \"text\": \"E